The paper deals with regret minimization in online learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the Lipschitz multi-armed bandit problem, which is a type of online learning problem. The paper also uses techniques from information theory, topology, and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.GT (Game Theory).
